## Steps to reproduce the issue

to use abc9-techmapping for ice40 or any other fpga with absolute path for lut file on windows:

> abc9 -W 400 -lut C:/.../ice40/abc_lp.lut -box C:/.../ice40/abc_lp.box

## Expected behavior

to map and not show any error

## Actual behavior

> 21. Executing ABC9 pass (technology mapping using ABC9).
> 
> 21.1. Extracting gate netlist of module `\NextZ80' to `<abc-temp-dir>/input.xaig'..
> ERROR: Abort in passes/techmap/abc9.cc:310.

I think it will be useful to be able to use absolute paths to specify lut and box files in abc9 command.
